    "narrative": "For April 21, the Ghost Ride the WHIP offense is anchored by **Corbin Carroll**, who commands the highest score of the day at 85.94. His favorable matchup against Burke, combined with his elite speed profile and a delivery window from the opposing pitcher that creates a high-probability environment for stolen bases, makes him our clear standout. The outfield is further bolstered by **James Wood** (76.28) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98), both of whom benefit from significant park factors and favorable platoon alignments against V\u00e1squez. **Brice Turang** (74.51) and **Trevor Story** (74.11) round out the top tier of starters; **Trevor Story** is particularly interesting today as his score is inflated by a +19% bump in SP skill, signaling that he is well-positioned to capitalize on Gil\u2019s projected struggles.\n\nWe face a difficult bench decision regarding **Giancarlo Stanton**, who narrowly missed the cutoff with a score of 48.48. Despite his immense raw power, his matchup against a high-skill arm like Early pushed his efficiency metrics below those of our utility slot. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (68.91) ultimately claimed that spot, as his platoon advantage against Baz and a solid order position in the three-hole provide a more reliable path to hitting efficiency than **Giancarlo Stanton**\u2019s volatile profile. Similarly, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** offers high-upside speed, the combination of a difficult pitcher matchup and a lower lineup placement left him on the outside looking in. Managers should monitor **Dalton Rushing** closely; although he occupies our C1 slot, his score of 56.39 is currently threatened by a 42% rain risk, which could necessitate a late swap if the game status shifts.",
